Top Stories (February 14)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR REQUESTS ADDITIONAL $500 MILLION TO BUY ENERGY
As Gov. Gray Davis works to craft a bailout plan for California's two largest 
electric utilities, California's fledgling foray into the power business is 
coming at an ever more expensive price that is nearing $2 billion.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/02/14/krtbn/0000-0350-SJ-ENERGY

CALIFORNIA CONSIDERS BUYING POWER LINES AMID CHANCE OF LOSING PRICE CAP
With a potential legal guillotine looming on Monday, Gov. Gray Davis is 
trying to piece together the framework of a utility bailout that includes a 
state purchase of privately owned electricity transmission lines in exchange 
for a series of concessions from Pacific Gas & Electric Co. and Southern 
California Edison.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/02/14/krtbn/0000-0358-SJ-POWER-LINES

BORALEX INC. TO ACQUIRE 2 POWER PLANTS IN VERMONT
Boralex Inc. has agreed in principle to acquire two power facilities in 
Vermont from Citizens Utilities.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/14/eng-djn/eng-djn_112028_70_7387464866042

UTILITY COMPANY BOWS OUT OF PENNSYLVANIA ELECTRICITY MARKET
PG Energy is getting out of the electricity business this year. That leaves 
the company's residential customers who live in the PPL service area with 
three options, according to a state Web site.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/02/14/krtbn/0000-0514-WB-ELECTRIC

GREEN MOUNTAIN ENERGY COMPANY WINS OVER 400,000 OHIO CUSTOMERS UNDER 
COUNTRY'S LARGEST ENERGY AGGREGATION CONTRACT
Green Mountain Energy Company, featuring the leading brand of cleaner and 
renewable energy, today was selected to serve over 400,000 Ohio electricity 
customers in the country's largest-ever energy aggregation contract.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/prnewswi
re/2001/02/14/tXbXo/2757-0651-TX-Green-Mountain-Co..photo.

NYISO: NYC NEEDS ANOTHER 296 MW TO MEET SUMMER POWER DEMAND
The operator of New York's bulk power grid said Wednesday New York City must 
add more generation to meet projected electricity demand this summer.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/14/eng-djn/eng-djn_210039_24_9287815438583

